n Panama|Panama]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Puerto Rico.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Puerto Rico#Government response|Puerto Rico]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Saba.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Saba#Timeline|Saba]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Saint Barth\u00e9lemy.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Saint Barth\u00e9lemy#Timeline|Saint Barth\u00e9lemy]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Saint Kitts and Nevis.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Saint Kitts and Nevis#Timeline|Saint Kitts and Nevis]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Saint Lucia.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Saint Lucia#Timeline|Saint Lucia]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Saint Pierre and Miquelon.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Saint Pierre and Miquelon|Saint Pierre and Miquelon]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Saint Vincent and the Grenadines.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Saint Vincent and the Grenadines#|Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Sint Eustatius.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Sint Eustatius#Timeline|Sint Eustatius]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Sint Maarten.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Sint Maarten#Preventive measures|Sint Maarten]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Trinidad and Tobago.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Trinidad and Tobago#Prevention efforts|Trinidad and Tobago]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Turks and Caicos Islands.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Turks and Caicos Islands#Prevention measures|Turks and Caicos Islands]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of United States Virgin Islands.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States Virgin Islands#Prevention|United States Virgin Islands]]'''\n\n{{div col end}}\n\n==South America==\n=== Brazil ===\nBrazilian president [[Jair Bolsonaro]] has been criticized due to \"lax handling\" of the outbreak and after calling it a \"fantasy\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-brazil/coronavirus-thumps-brazil-prompting-nationwide-cries-of-bolsonaro-out-idUSKBN2152FK|title=Coronavirus thumps Brazil, prompting nationwide cries of 'Bolsonaro Out!'|website=Reuters.com|date=19 March 2020|language=en|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> His lack of action has also prompted many protests across the country since 18 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/22/brazilians-protest-bolsonaro-coronavirus-panelaco|title=Brazilians protest over Bolsonaro's muddled coronavirus response|website=The Guardian|language=en|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/brasil/panelacos-contra-bolsonaro-acontecem-em-varias-cidades-do-pais-1-24313585|title=Panela\u00e7os contra Bolsonaro acontecem em v\u00e1rias cidades do pa\u00eds|website=O GLOBO|language=pt|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> Days before, on 15 March, Bolsonaro received harsh criticism after attending a pro-government demonstration in [[Bras\u00edlia]] on which he had physical contact with more than two hundred people, against the recommendations of his own Minister of Health.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/15/mesmo-com-recomendacao-de-monitoramento-por-coronavirus-bolsonaro-participa-de-carro-de-ato-em-brasilia.ghtml|title=Bolsonaro descumpre monitoramento por coronav\u00edrus, participa de ato e cumprimenta apoiadores no DF|website=G1|language=pt|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.correiobraziliense.com.br/app/noticia/politica/2020/03/16/interna_politica,834570/bolsonaro-teve-contato-direto-com-ao-menos-272-pessoas-durante-ato-df.shtml|title=Bolsonaro teve contato direto com ao menos 272 pessoas durante ato no DF|website=Correio Braziliense|language=pt|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref> Following the event, the president of the [[Brazilian Chamber of Deputies]], [[Rodrigo Maia]], said that Bolsonaro's acts were an \"attack on public health\", going against his own government guidelines, while [[Davi Alcolumbre]], president of the [[Brazilian Senate]], classified Bolsonaro's behaviour as \"inconsequential\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/brasil/bolsonaro-comete-atentado-saude-publica-em-manifestacao-diz-maia-24306764|title=\"Bolsonaro comete 'atentado \u00e0 sa\u00fade p\u00fablica' em manifesta\u00e7\u00e3o\", diz Maia|website=O GLOBO|language=pt|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref> The Brazilian Ministry of Health has also been criticized for not providing enough test kits, which may muddle the efforts to contain the outbreak in the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://piaui.folha.uol.com.br/pouco-teste-para-muito-virus/|title=POUCO TESTE PARA MUITO V\u00cdRUS|website=Piau\u00ed|language=pt|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.redebrasilatual.com.br/saude-e-ciencia/2020/03/ausencia-de-testes-de-coronavirus-e-derrota-para-o-pais-diz-infectologista/|title=Aus\u00eancia de testes de coronav\u00edrus \u00e9 derrota para o pa\u00eds, diz infectologista|website=redebrasilatual.com.br|language=pt|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Other countries and territories===\n{{div col|colwidth=15em}}\n\n* [[Image:Flag of Argentina.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Argentina#Management|Argentina]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Bolivia.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Bolivia#Measures taken by the government|Bolivia]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Chile.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Chile#Government response|Chile]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Colombia.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Colombia#Timeline|Colombia]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Ecuador.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Ecuador#Timeline|Ecuador]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Falkland Islands.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Falkland Islands#Timeline|Falkland Islands]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of French Guiana.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in French Guiana#Preventive measures|French Guiana]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Guyana.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Guyana#Preventive measures|Guyana]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Paraguay.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Paraguay#Timeline|Paraguay]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Peru.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Peru#Timeline|Peru]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Suriname.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Suriname#Crisis Management|Suriname]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Uruguay.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Uruguay#Response|Uruguay]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Venezuela.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Venezuela#Measures|Venezuela]]'''\n\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Oceania==\n===Fiji===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Fiji}}\n\nAt the beginning of February, the Government of Fiji announced a travel ban to China.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fbcnews.com.fj/news/fiji-to-close-boarders-to-foreign-nationals-amidst-coronavirus-outbreak/|title=Fiji toughens on border entry amidst coronavirus concerns|website=Fiji Broadcasting Corporation|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> As the disease started spreading to other countries, Fiji extended the travel ban to Italy, Iran and South Korea.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://amp.rnz.co.nz/article/d796c6bb-8ea3-408f-9b64-a9a17609b4b9|title=Coronavirus: Fiji extends travel ban amid growing concerns|website=amp.rnz.co.nz|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nHowever, on 19 March, Fiji confirmed its first case of COVID-19 in Lautoka.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fijivillage.com/news/COVID-19-patient-is-a-27-year-old-flight-attendant-who-had-recent-travel-history-to-USA-and-NZ---Dr-Sahukhan-4x8rf5/|title=COVID-19 patient is a 27-year-old flight attendant who had recent travel history to USA and NZ \u2013 Dr. Sahukhan|last=Fijivillage|website=www.fijivillage.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> As a precautionary measure, the Government of Fiji announced the lockdown of the city until 7 April 2020<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fijitimes.com/covid-19-lautoka-schools-closed-until-further-notice/|title=COVID-19: Lautoka schools closed until further notice|website=FijiTimes|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> and the travel ban was further extended to the United States and the whole of Europe including the United Kingdom.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fbcnews.com.fj/news/covid-19/pm-announces-major-restrictions-including-closure-of-some-services-due-to-covid-19/|title=PM announces major restrictions due to COVID-19|last=News|first=Indra Singh Manager|website=Fiji Broadcasting Corporation|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> Later on 2 April, the Government announced a lockdown of Suva, after confirmed cases in the capital.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fbcnews.com.fj/news/covid-19/fiji-confirms-latest-cases-of-covid-19/|title=Nabua couple are latest COVID-19 patients, Suva in lockdown from tomorrow|last=News|first=Indra Singh Manager|website=Fiji Broadcasting Corporation|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nAs the cases rose, [[Prime Minister of Fiji|Prime Minister]] [[Frank Bainimarama|Voreqe Bainimarama]] announced a nationwide curfew from 8pm to 5am and social gatherings was banned. Schools and non-essential services was closed and the public was advised to stay at home and practice good hygiene.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fijitimes.com/nationwide-curfew-to-come-into-effect-from-sunday/|title=COVID-19: Nationwide curfew to come into effect from Monday|website=FijiTimes|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n===New Zealand===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in New Zealand}}\nOn 28 January, the Ministry of Health set up the National Health Coordination Centre (NHCC) in response to the outbreak. On 3 February, the New Zealand Government announced that foreign travellers who left from China would be denied entry to New Zealand, with only New Zealand citizens and permanent residents and their family being allowed to enter.\n\nNew Zealand confirmed its first case of Covid-19 on 28 February, a New Zealand citizen in his 60s who had recently visited Iran. The travel ban was extended to include Iran on the same day.\n\n17 March: Health Minister David Clark announced that the Government would deport foreign tourists who flout self-quarantine restrictions. Immigration New Zealand placed two foreign tourists into forced quarantine for defying Government requirements to self-quarantine for two weeks. Finance Minister Grant Robertson announced a NZ$12.1 billion Covid-19 business package. Logan Park High School in Dunedin closed for 48 hours after one of its students tested positive for the coronavirus.\n\n18 March: The Royal New Zealand Returned and Services' Association announced that all Anzac Day services, scheduled for 25 April, would be cancelled.\n\n19 March: The government required the cancellation of mass indoor events with more than 100 people. Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern announced the closure of New Zealand's borders to all but New Zealand citizens and residents, with effect after 11:59 pm on Thursday night.\n\n21 March: Local councils in New Zealand's main centres announced the closures of public facilities including swimming pools, libraries, recreation centres, community centres, art galleries, and museums.\n\n23 March: Prime Minister Ardern raised the Covid-19 alert level from two to three and announced the closure of all schools beginning on that day. The Government also announced that they would raise the national alert level to four at 11:59pm on 25 March, which would lead to a nationwide lockdown, for a period of four weeks. While all sporting matches and events as well as non-essential services such as pools, bars, cafes, restaurants, playgrounds are required to close in 48 hours, essential services such as supermarkets, petrol stations, and health services will remain open.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=12319029|title=Covid 19 coronavirus alert 3: New Zealand to move to alert 4 lockdown for next four weeks \u2013 Jacinda Ardern says schools closed, essential services only|first=Derek Cheng Derek Cheng is a political reporter for the New Zealand Herald|last=derek.cheng@nzme.co.nz|date=23 March 2020|accessdate=27 March 2020|via=www.nzherald.co.nz}}</ref>\n\n===Other countries and territories===\n{{div col|colwidth=15em}}\n\n* [[Image:Flag of Australia.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Australia#Federal government|Australia]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of French Polynesia.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in French Polynesia#Timeline|French Polynesia]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of New Caledonia.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in New Caledonia#Timeline|New Caledonia]]'''\n* [[Image:Flag of Papua New Guinea.svg|25px]] '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Papua New Guinea#Prevention measures|Papua New Guinea]]'''\n\n{{div col end}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal-inline|Coronavirus disease 2019}}\n*[[List of 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic legislation]]\n*[[Curfews and lockdowns related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on sports]] \n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on religion]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on education]]\n{{clear}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=JHMap>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases by Johns Hopkins CSSE |url=https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6 |publisher=[[Johns Hopkins University]] (JHU)|website=gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com |accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"SCMP 20200206\">{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/3049298/coronavirus-zhejiang-adopts-draconian-quarantine-measures-fight|title=Coronavirus: Shanghai neighbour Zhejiang imposes draconian quarantine|date=6 February 2020|website=[[South China Morning Post]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206112642/https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/ar